The sources also told CNBC the music streaming site is valued at $13 billion. In a direct listing, the stock price is based on supply and demand. In an initial public offering, a more widely chosen route, a company offers investors shares before it goes public at a set, usually compressed price. Spotify is the world&#8217;s top music streaming site. It doubled the number of its paying subscribers over the past two years to 50 million as of March. Rival Apple Music has 20 million paying subscribers as of last December.